Such geo-strategic reflections, however, reflect only one facet.
Another facet raises the question of how the different business models of each of these banks can be matched.
In June, Merl stated that the decisive question of which business model the future capacity of the Länder's banks should be ensured had hitherto not been resolved by the German grouping of savings and transfer funds.
In the long run, a carving of WestLb could take place, carving which is obviously not desired here.
This is also what is discussed in the letter of the governing committee in place: in any case, a <0x60>global solution' would be envisaged for the establishment.
How all this will be put in the same basket with the union of some entities with the Deta-Bank remains to be seen.
