To combat these differences, Mr. Obama’s education program supports, among many other topics, “bilingual transitional education” for those who learn English.
However, the question for Obama is whether his desire to achieve a bilingual education that advocates classroom instruction in languages other than English goes beyond his interest in eliminating differences.
Take, for example, Sixth Street Prep, an elementary school in East Los Angeles County.
