This incredible success was achieved thanks to another ingredient than that advanced by Mr. Obama.
Sixth Street relies on analysis, practice, a constant assessment of capabilities as well as an exemplary attitude.
In addition, and here is an example that Mr. Obama could copy, reports Linda Mikels, principal of Sixth Street, this school has instituted "full immersion" English language instruction.
Full immersion in English focuses on the almost constant use of English in instruction.
Ms. Mikels, opposed to bilingual education, told me "we had a huge success with a student who had just arrived from Mexico, 12 months later, if you went without his class, you would have had no chance of identifying him."
